'''《犬类智商》'''是一本介绍犬类智商的书籍，作者是[[斯坦利·科伦|斯坦利·科伦]]。斯坦利·科伦是[[加拿大|加拿大]][[温哥华|温哥华]][[不列颠哥伦比亚大学|不列颠哥伦比亚大学]]的一名[[心理学|心理学]]教授。<ref name="Coren1995">{{cite book | last=Coren | first=Stanley | title=The Intelligence of Dogs: A Guide To The Thoughts, Emotions, And Inner Lives Of Our Canine Companions | url=https://archive.org/details/intelligenceofdo00core | publisher=New York: Bantam Books | isbn=0-553-37452-4 | year=1995 }}</ref>该书于1994年出版，介绍了作者对于不同狗类品种智商的分类。<ref name="Boxer1994">{{cite web |title=My Dog's Smarter Than Your Dog |first=Sarah |last=Boxer |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9A04E2DA163BF936A35755C0A962958260&partner=rssnyt&emc=rss |publisher=NewYork Times |date=1994-06-05 |accessdate=2013-10-26 |archive-date=2012-07-04 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68ubP3SNN?url=http://www.nytimes.com/1994/06/05/books/my-dog-s-smarter-than-your-dog.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Wade1994">{{cite web |title=METHOD AND MADNESS; What Dogs Think |first=Nicholas |last=Wade |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E0DE7DC1F3DF930A35754C0A962958260 |publisher=NewYork Times |date=1994-07-03 |accessdate=2013-10-26 |archive-date=2012-07-04 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68ubPdjGp?url=http://www.nytimes.com/1994/07/03/magazine/method-and-madness-what-dogs-think.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Croke1994">{{cite web |title=Growling at the dog list |last=Croke |first=Vicki |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-5513441_ITM |publisher=Tribune New Service (published in the Boston Globe) |date=1994-04-21 |accessdate=2013-10-26 |archive-date=2012-07-04 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68ubQGW9o?url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/search/?q=Growling%20at%20the%20dog%20list.%20%28Originated%20from%20Boston%20Globe%29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>科伦与2006年出版了该书的第二版。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/intelligence-of-dogs-a-guide-to-the-thoughts-emotions-and-inner-lives-or-our-canine-companions/oclc/30700778/editions?referer=di&editionsView=true|publisher=[[WorldCat|WorldCat]]|title=Showing all editions for 'The intelligence of dogs : a guide to the thoughts, emotions, and inner lives or our canine companions'|accessdate=2011-10-23|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810000143/https://www.worldcat.org/title/intelligence-of-dogs-a-guide-to-the-thoughts-emotions-and-inner-lives-or-our-canine-companions/oclc/30700778/editions?referer=di&editionsView=true|dead-url=no}}</ref>

科伦在该书中定义了狗类智商的三个方面：本能、适应能力以及工作服从能力。<ref name=coren1>{{cite web|publisher=Psychology Today|url=http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/canine-corner/200907/canine-intelligence-breed-does-matter|title=Canine Intelligence—Breed Does Matter|author=Stanley Coren|date=July 15, 2009|accessdate=2011-08-16|archive-date=2013-01-30|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6E2u8KKFY?url=http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/canine-corner/200907/canine-intelligence-breed-does-matter|dead-url=no}}</ref> 本能是指一个品种的犬类在完成任务时的能力，例如：畜牧、指示、护卫以及与人类相处的关系。<ref name=coren1/>适应能力是指狗类利用本身能力解决事务的水平。<ref name=coren1/> 工作服从能力是指狗类听从人类驯化的能力。<ref name=coren1/>

==方法==

这本书主要关注狗类工作服从能力。科伦将评价请求发给了[[美国犬业俱乐部|美国犬业俱乐部]]以及{{link-en|加拿大犬业俱乐部|Canadian Kennel Club}}，邀请他们参与了对狗类工作服从能力的评价。他收到了199封回复，这些回复代表了50%工作于北美地区的狗类评审的观点。<ref name=coren1/> 

科伦发现评审们在给狗类智商排名时有大量的共识，比如，评审们都将[[边境牧羊犬|边境牧羊犬]]排到了前十名，而将[[阿富汗猎狗|阿富汗猎狗]]排到了后面。
没有被[[美国犬业俱乐部|美国犬业俱乐部]]以及{{link-en|加拿大犬业俱乐部|Canadian Kennel Club}}（比如[[杰克罗素㹴|杰克罗素㹴]]）认证的品种并没有参与排名。
混种狗也没有参与排名，但很多养狗人士表示混种狗往往比纯种狗更聪明，因此本排名仅表示作者的个人观点，并不能说明犬类智商与品种有直接关系。

